## üìù TYPOGRAPHY BEST PRACTICES (Official Databricks Guidelines)

### ‚úÖ DO: Use Hierarchy for Scannable Content

**Adjust size, weight, and color to create visual hierarchy:**
- Vary text sizes within content blocks for scannability
- Use weight (400, 500, 600, 700) to differentiate importance
- Apply subtle color changes (Navy-900 for primary, Gray-text for secondary)
- Example: Large heading (24px, 600) + body text (14px, 400) + metadata (12px, Gray-text)

**Effective Hierarchy Patterns:**
```
‚úÖ Overline (10px, uppercase, Gray-text)
   Large Title (48px, 700, Navy-900)
   Subtitle (16px, 400, Gray-text)
   Body Paragraph (14px, 400, Navy-900)
   
‚úÖ Card Title (18px, 600, Navy-900)
   Description (14px, 400, Navy-900)
   Metadata (12px, 400, Gray-text)
```

### ‚úÖ DO: Give Content Space to Breathe

**Proper spacing between text elements:**
- Minimum spacing between text blocks: 16px (space-4)
- Paragraph spacing: 20-24px (space-5 to space-6)
- Section spacing: 32-48px (space-8 to space-12)
- Don't cram text elements too close together
- White space improves readability and focus

**Spacing Guidelines:**
```
Title
[16px gap]
Subtitle
[24px gap]
Body Paragraph 1
[20px gap]
Body Paragraph 2
[32px gap]
Next Section Title
```

### ‚úÖ DO: Use Proper Line Height

**Official Databricks line-height standards:**
- **Body copy:** 150% (1.5) line-height ‚úÖ
  - Example: 14px text = 21px line-height (1.5)
  - Example: 16px text = 24px line-height (1.5)
- **Headlines:** 120% (1.2) line-height ‚úÖ
  - Example: 48px text = 56-60px line-height (1.17-1.25)
  - Example: 32px text = 40px line-height (1.25)
- **Never use tight line-height** - makes text hard to read

**Line Height Reference:**
| Text Size | Body Copy (1.5) | Headline (1.2) |
|-----------|----------------|----------------|
| 10px | 15px | 12px |
| 12px | 18px | 14px |
| 14px | 21px | 17px |
| 16px | 24px | 19px |
| 24px | 36px | 29px |
| 32px | 48px | 38px |
| 48px | 72px | 58px |

### ‚ùå DON'T: Use Right-Aligned Text

**Left-alignment only for body text:**
- ‚ùå Never use right-aligned text for paragraphs
- ‚ùå Never use right-aligned text for buttons or CTAs
- ‚úÖ Always use left-aligned text for readability
- ‚úÖ Center-alignment acceptable for headers (sparingly)

### ‚ùå DON'T: Create Impenetrable Text Blocks

**Break up large paragraphs:**
- ‚ùå Long paragraphs with no breaks - hard to scan
- ‚ùå Inline links throughout paragraphs - disrupts flow
- ‚úÖ Break content into manageable chunks (3-5 lines max per paragraph)
- ‚úÖ Use clear CTAs at the end of sections
- ‚úÖ Add headings to break up long content
- ‚úÖ Use bullet points for lists

