## ‚ôø ACCESSIBILITY REQUIREMENTS

### 1. **Color Contrast (CRITICAL - Follow Official Guidelines)**

**WCAG AA Standards (Minimum):**
- **Normal text:** 4.5:1 contrast ratio minimum
- **Large text (18px+):** 3:1 contrast ratio minimum
- **UI components:** 3:1 contrast ratio for interactive elements

**Pre-Approved High-Contrast Combinations:**
- ‚úÖ Navy-900 `#0B2026` on White `#FFFFFF` - **18.7:1 contrast** (Excellent)
- ‚úÖ Navy-900 `#0B2026` on Oat-light `#F9F7F4` - **17.8:1 contrast** (Excellent)
- ‚úÖ White `#FFFFFF` on Blue-600 `#2272B4` - **5.4:1 contrast** (Passes AA)
- ‚úÖ White `#FFFFFF` on Navy-700 `#143D4A` - **14.2:1 contrast** (Excellent)
- ‚úÖ White `#FFFFFF` on Lava-600 `#FF3621` - **4.9:1 contrast** (Passes AA)
- ‚úÖ Gray-text `#5A6F77` on White `#FFFFFF` - **6.2:1 contrast** (Passes AAA)

**NEVER Use These Combinations:**
- ‚ùå Navy-400 on Oat-light - Low contrast
- ‚ùå Yellow-600 on White - Insufficient contrast for body text
- ‚ùå Blue-600 on Navy-700 - Similar brightness levels
- ‚ùå Lava-400 on White - Too light for text

**Validation Tools:**
- WebAIM Contrast Checker: https://webaim.org/resources/contrastchecker/
- Chrome DevTools Accessibility Panel
- Figma plugins: Stark, A11y - Color Contrast Checker

### 2. **Focus Indicators**
   - 2px solid ring
   - Blue-600 `#2272B4` color
   - Always visible on keyboard navigation
   - Never remove focus outlines (use alternative if needed)

### 3. **Touch Targets**
   - Minimum 44px √ó 44px for interactive elements
   - 8px spacing between adjacent interactive elements
   - Applies to buttons, links, form controls, chips

### 4. **Status Communication**
   - **Never rely on color alone** for conveying information
   - Always include icon or text label with colored indicators
   - Use semantic HTML elements (`<button>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`)
   - Provide ARIA labels when visual indicators aren't sufficient

### 5. **Color Blindness Considerations**
   - Test designs with color blindness simulators
   - Ensure severity levels are distinguishable without color
   - Use patterns or shapes in addition to color coding
   - Critical/High/Warning should have different icons, not just colors

